Step 1
======
=> Create a repo of your git hub

Step 2
======
=> push your local project to repo you just created

Step 3
======
 => enter your domain server with "ssh" command
 command >>>> ssh -p 7822 userName@domainName

 [e.g>> domainName is "arkarhein1199.me",
		 		userName is "arkarhein1199" ]

Step 4
=======
 >>> pull "yourRepolink.git"

	=>	After your comeback is success, enter your destined location folder and  then pull repo link that you pushed your local project on gitHub

	command >>>> cd "folderName"
	command >>>> git pull "yourRepolink.git"

 ----------------------------------------------------------------------
 >>> clone "yourRepolink.git"

 	=> After your comeback is success, enter your destined location folder and  then clone the whole repo project that you pushed your local project on gitHub

 	command >>>> cd "folderName"
 	command >>>>  git clone "yourRepolink.git"